title: ‘Politically irrelevant’: Coalition split handing ‘absolute gift’ to Anthony Albanese
description: Shadow Energy and Emissions Reduction Minister Dan Tehan claims the Liberals need to be “focused” on bringing the Coalition “back together”.  “Otherwise, we are going to be politically irrelevant for months,” Mr Tehan told Sky News Australia.  “All we’re doing is handing an absolute gift to Anthony Albanese.”

title: Chris Minns expands drone use under $4.2 million shark mitigation plan
description: The Minns government has revealed plans to expand drone use under a $4.2 million shark mitigation package.  The plan would improve aerial footage for thirty more beaches across the state.  The announcement follows multiple beach closures across NSW due to increased shark sightings.

title: ‘Furious’ Starmer demands apology after Trump’s Afghan war remarks cause ‘considerable upset’
description: TalkTV host Mark Dolan claims US President Donald Trump’s Afghanistan comments have caused “considerable upset”.  President Trump outraged veterans and world leaders from across the Western world this week by claiming allied troops had not fought on the front lines during the conflict.  “He was off message. This is not something that those around him would have wanted him to say,” Mr Dolan told Sky News host James Macpherson.  “So, Starmer’s furious, we understand the King’s concerned about it.”

title: ‘Armageddon’: Trouble for Starmer as Labour expected to be ‘obliterated’ at UK local elections
description: TalkTV host Mark Dolan has predicted that UK Labour under Keir Starmer will be “obliterated” at the local elections this year.  “The governing Labour Party, led by Keir Starmer are expected to be obliterated, armageddon,” Mr Dolan told Sky News host James Macpherson.  “I think Starmer’s gone by Christmas.”

title: ‘Turning into Joe Biden’: TV host hilariously roasts Bruce Springsteen
description: Sky News host Rowan Dean has roasted singer-songwriter and guitarist Bruce Springsteen, joking that the rockstar was “turning” into former US President Joe Biden.

title: Barack Obama slammed following rare response to second ICE shooting in Minnesota
description: Former US President Barack Obama has issued a rare statement following the killing of a second protester by Immigration & Customs Enforcement agents.  On Sunday, Obama posted to social media reacting to the death of 37-year-old Alex Pretti, who was shot and killed by ICE agents in Minnesota.  “The killing of Alex Pretti is a heartbreaking tragedy. It should also be a wake-up call to every American, regardless of party, that many of our core values as a nation are increasingly under assault,” Obama wrote.  Attached to Obama’s post was a full statement released by him and former first lady Michelle Obama.  Obama claimed protesters have been “rightly outraged” over “masked” ICE agents carrying out immigration operations.

title: ‘Ibiza DJ with sunglasses’: TV hosts savagely rip into Emmanuel Macron's look
description: Sky News host James Morrow has mocked French President Emmanuel Macron over his choice of eyewear at the World Economic Forum in Davos.

title: ‘Cannot continue like this’: Liberals ‘focused’ on bringing Coalition ‘back together’
description: Shadow Energy and Emissions Reduction Minister Dan Tehan claims the Liberals “cannot continue” without the Coalition reforming.  “We cannot continue like we are, and if things escalate that, then it’s going to make it harder to bring it back together,” Mr Tehan told Sky News Australia.  “All my colleagues have to take collective responsibility, Liberal and National, on making sure that everything we are doing is focused on that outcome.”

title: Prince Harry voices anger over Donald Trump’s Afghan war remarks
description: TalkTV host Mark Dolan discusses US President Donald Trump’s comments about the United Kingdom’s role in Afghanistan which have sparked some upset.  “It’s very awkward diplomatically,” Mr Dolan told Sky News host James Macpherson.  “And Prince Harry, as you mentioned, has also made remarks, given that he served in Afghanistan as well.”

title: Donald Trump’s brutal message for ‘every Democrat’ to cooperate with his administration
description: US President Donald Trump has unleashed on “every Democrat Governor” in a scathing post to Truth Social.  In a brutal post to social media, President Trump called on every Democrat Mayor and Governor to “formally cooperate” with his administration and enforce the United States’ laws.  His post saw him call out Minnesota Governor Tim Walz and Minneapolis Mayor Jacob Frey following weeks of anti-ICE protests in the state.  Trump unleashed on blue states’ handling of ICE agents, with protests erupting across the country against the immigration officers.

title: ‘Don’t see this rift healing any time soon’: ‘Spoiled rotten’ Brooklyn Beckham tarnishes family
description: TalkTV host Mark Dolan has hit out at Brooklyn Beckham following his lengthy statement calling out his family amid an ongoing feud.  “He’s the ultimate nepo baby, totally entitled, obviously spoiled rotten,” Mr Dolan told Sky News host James Macpherson.  “I don’t see this rift healing any time soon.”

title: ‘Smart’: UK Home Office to launch ‘British FBI’
description: TalkTV host Mark Dolan discusses the UK Home Office setting up a new National Police Service, also dubbed the “British FBI”, to deal with organised crime, terrorism, fraud, and online child abuse.  “I think that’s smart,” Mr Dolan told Sky News host James Macpherson.  “But in the end, this government is going to have to put their money where their mouth is because unless you invest in policing, your citizens will never be safer.”

title: ‘Things are going to get worse’: ‘Sinister forces’ attempt to turn Americans against Trump admin
description: Sky News host James Morrow has warned that the left is “creating a permission structure” for people to use political activism to “take things to ever greater and more violent extremes”.  This comes as the left and Democrats continue to push back against the Trump administration’s crackdown on illegal immigration and fraud amid ongoing protests, particularly in Minnesota.  “To me, it suggests that there are very sinister forces out there taking advantage of American values of trust and openness to convince liberals that the very government that is trying to protect their society and its virtues is the enemy,” Mr Morrow said.

title: Ayatollah Ali Khamenei 'hiding' in fear America will strike Iran as end of regime looms
description: Iran’s Supreme Leader, Ayatollah Ali Khamenei, has gone into hiding over fears America will strike as a US air carrier sails toward the Gulf.  According to the Jerusalem Post, the 86-year-old leader has secured himself in a bunker in Tehran as the aircraft carrier USS Abraham Lincoln approaches.  The Jerusalem Post revealed that Iran International reported that Khamenei’s move follows an imminent attack by the US.  In the 86-year-old’s absence, he has left his 53-year-old son, Masoud Khamenei, in charge of running the day-to-day operations.  Shortly after US President Donald Trump announced that warships were headed to the Middle East, Iran believed the likelihood of an attack by America was high.

title: ‘Last night was special’: Nedd Brockmann awarded Young Australian of the Year
description: Young Australian of the Year Nedd Brockmann claims the Australian of the Year ceremony was “really special”.  “I am proud of what I’ve put myself through, I’ve chosen to be in those situations, no one forced me to run across the country,” Mr Brockmann told Sky News Australia.  “I’ve absolutely done it for a much greater cause than me.”
